{{Italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file = Aurora Mark di Suvero.jpg | painting_alignment = Front | image_size = 300px | title = Aurora | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Mark di Suvero | year = 1992-1993 | type = sculpture | height_imperial = 16.4 | width_imperial = 19.6 | length_imperial = 28.8 ½ | imperial_unit = ft | metric_unit = m | city = Washington, D.C. | museum = [[National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden]] | coordinates = | owner = National Gallery of Art }}
'''''Aurora''''' is a [[public art]]work by [[United States|American]] artist [[Mark di Suvero]]. It is in the collection of the [[National Gallery of Art]] and on display at the [[National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden]] in [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]].<ref name="SIRIS">{{cite web | author= | year=1999 | title=Aurora, (sculpture).| work=National Gallery of Art Sculpture Garden Checklist| publisher=[[Smithsonian American Art Museum]] | url=http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!344032~!0#focus | accessdate= 26 April 2011}}</ref><ref name="NGA1">{{cite web | author= | year=2011 | title=Mark di Suvero | work=Sculpture Garden | publisher=[[National Gallery of Art]] | url=http://www.nga.gov/feature/sculpturegarden/sculpture/sculpture5-fs.shtm | accessdate= 26 April 2011}}</ref>
== Description == ''Aurora'' consists of 8 tons of [[steel]], resting on three diagonal supports.<ref name="NGA2">{{cite web | author=| year=2011| title=Mark di Suvero | work=Sculpture Garden | publisher=National Gallery of Art | url=http://www.nga.gov/feature/sculpturegarden/sculpture/sculpture5.shtm| accessdate= 26 April 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110508195740/http://www.nga.gov/feature/sculpturegarden/sculpture/sculpture5.shtm| archivedate= 8 May 2011 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref><ref name="Waymarking">{{cite web | author=Outspoken1 | year=2008 | title=Aurora by Mark di Suvero - National Gallery Sculpture Garden, Washington, D.C.| work=Abstract Public Sculptures | publisher=Waymarking.com | url=http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WM4A8V_Aurora_by_Mark_di_Suvero_National_Gallery_Sculpture_Garden_Washington_DC| accessdate= 26 April 2011}}</ref> Certain "linear elements converge within a central circular hub and then explode outward."<ref name="NGA2"/>
== Information == The name of the sculpture comes from a poem by [[Federico García Lorca]] about [[New York City]].<ref name="NGA2"/>
=== Acquisition === The sculpture is a gift from the Gift of Morris and Gwendolyn Cafritz Foundation.<ref name="SIRIS"/>
=== Reception === According to the National Gallery of Art the supports and steel "combine massive scale with elegance of proportion," and "imparting tension and dynamism."<ref name="NGA2"/>
