'''Bipont Editions''', the name of a famous series of editions, in 50 volumes, of [[Greek language|Greek]] and [[Latin]] classical authors, so called from Bipontium, the modern Latin name of [[Zweibrücken]] or DeuxPonts in Bavaria, where they were first issued in 1779. Their place of publication was afterwards transferred to [[Strasbourg]].

See Butters, ''Uber die Editiones Bipontinae'' (1877).

