''''' Self-Portrait with Model at Bergamo''''' is a bronze sculpture by [[Giacomo Manzù]], originally modeled in 1942. One cast, made by 1960, is located at the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]] of the [[Smithsonian Institution]] in Washington D.C..<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hirshhorn.si.edu/visit/collection_object.asp?key=32&subkey=9884 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110629172750/http://hirshhorn.si.edu/visit/collection_object.asp?key=32&subkey=9884 |archivedate=2011-06-29 |df= }}</ref><ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!373055~!0#focus "Self-Portrait with Model at Bergamo, (sculpture)"]. ''SIRIS''</ref>
